{"title_page": "Joe Biden sexual assault allegation", "text_new": "<noinclude>{{User:RMCD bot/subject notice|1=?|2=Talk:Joe Biden sexual assault allegation#Requested move 14 April 2020 }}\n</noinclude><!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Joe Biden assault allegation|timestamp=20200412194501|year=2020|month=April|day=12|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Joe Biden assault allegation|date=12 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Redirect|Tara Reade|the actress|Tara Reid}}\n{{Use American English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\nIn March 2020, Alexandra Tara Reade alleged that [[Joe Biden]] had sexually assaulted her when she was a senate aide in 1993.<ref name=InterceptTimesup>{{cite news|url=https://theintercept.com/2020/03/24/joe-biden-metoo-times-up/|first=Ryan|last=Grim|title=Time's Up Said It Could Not Fund a #MeToo Allegation Against Joe Biden, Citing Its Nonprofit Status and His Presidential Run|website=[[The Intercept]]|date=March 24, 2020 |access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref><ref name=vox>{{cite news|url=https://www.vox.com/2020/3/27/21195935/joe-biden-sexual-assault-allegation|last=North|first=Anna|title=A sexual assault allegation against Joe Biden has ignited a firestorm of controversy|website=[[Vox (website)|Vox]]|date=March 27, 2020 |access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://thehill.com/hilltv/rising/489719-tara-reade-discusses-biden-allegation-with-hilltvs-rising|title=Tara Reade discusses Biden allegation with Hill.TV's 'Rising'|newspaper=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]]|date=March 26, 2020 |access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/rose-mcgowan-alyssa-milano-joe-biden-alexandra-tara-reade-kavanaugh-a9454256.html|last=White|first=Adam|title=Rose McGowan calls Charmed co-star Alyssa Milano 'a fraud' for endorsing Joe Biden|newspaper=[[The Independent]]|date=April 8, 2020 <!-- From the timestamp in the HTML source --> |access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Halper|first=Katie|url=https://www.currentaffairs.org/2020/03/tara-reade-tells-her-story|title=Tara Reade Tells Her Story|date=March 31, 2020|magazine=[[Current Affairs (magazine)|Current Affairs]]|access-date=April 9, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> A Biden spokesperson said the allegation was false.<ref name=nyt>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/12/us/politics/joe-biden-tara-reade-sexual-assault-complaint.html|last=Lerer|first=Lisa|last2=Ember|first2=Sydney|title=Examining Tara Reade's Sexual Assault Allegation Against Joe Biden|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=April 12, 2020 |access-date=April 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\n[[File:SenareaidIDTaraReade.webp|thumb|U.S. Senate Identification Badge photo of Reade she provided to the ''[[New York Times]]'']]\nAlexandra Tara Reade is resident of California, having been born there circa 1964.<ref name=\"WE200415\">{{cite web|last1=Larsen|first1=Emily|title=Everything we know about the Biden sexual assault allegation|url=https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/news/everything-we-know-about-the-biden-sexual-assault-allegation|publisher=Washington Examiner |access-date=April 16, 2020|date=April 15, 2020}}</ref>  She was an actress and a model in her early life.<ref name=\"WE200415\" />  When she was 29, she was a staff assistant in the office of then Senator Joe Biden from December 1992 to August 1993.<ref name=\"WE200415\" />\n\nAccording to the ''Washington Examiner,'' after working in Washington, she left and became a mother, but changed her name multiple times after leaving an abusive marriage.<ref name=\"WE200415\" />  She earned a law degree from [[Seattle University School of Law]], but has not practiced law.<ref name=\"WE200415\" />  She has worked as a [[victims rights]] advocate and with families who have special needs children.<ref name=\"WE200415\" />  She has also testified as an expert witness in court.<ref name=\"WE200415\" />\n\n== Allegations ==\nDuring an interview with a reporter in April 2019, Reade alleged that Biden touched her inappropriately and sexual harassed her while she worked in his U.S. Senate office.  Reade made the allegation after watching an episode of the ''[[The View (talk show)|The View]]'' on April 1, 2019 in which Nevada politician [[Lucy Flores]] had alleged that Biden sniffed her hair and kissed the back of her head shortly before a political rally in 2014.<ref name=InterceptTimesup /><ref name=InterceptTimesup /><ref>{{Cite news|first=Alan|last=Riquelmy|authorlink=|title=Nevada County woman says Joe Biden inappropriately touched her while working in his U.S. Senate office|newspaper=[[The Union (newspaper)|The Union]]|date=April 3, 2019|url=https://www.theunion.com/news/nevada-county-woman-says-joe-biden-inappropriately-touched-her-while-working-in-his-u-s-senate-office/ |access-date=April 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nDuring an interview with Katie Halper which was released as a podcast on March 25, 2020, Reade alleged that Biden had pushed her against a wall and penetrated her with his finger in a [[Capitol Hill]] office building in 1993.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.salon.com/2020/03/31/a-woman-accuses-joe-biden-of-sexual-assault-and-all-hell-breaks-loose-online-heres-what-we-know/|title=A woman accuses Joe Biden of sexual assault, and all hell breaks loose online. Here's what we know|last=Marcotte|first=Amanda|date=March 31, 2020|website=Salon|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref>  On April 9, 2020, she filed a police report with the Washington, D.C. police alleging she was sexually assaulted between March 1 and May 31, 1993.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Vitali|first1=Ali|last2=Memoli|first2=Mike|title=Woman broadens claims against Biden to include sexual assault|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/woman-broadens-claims-against-biden-include-sexual-assault-n1182296 |access-date=April 16, 2020|work=NBC News|date=April 12, 2020}}</ref> Reade stated that the report was about Biden. She acknowledged that the statute of limitations has lapsed, and that she filed the report \"for safety reasons only\".<ref name=vox /><ref name=\"nyt\" /><ref name=Mangan-200414>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/04/14/joe-biden-accused-of-sex-assault-amid-challenge-to-donald-trump.html|title=Joe Biden is accused of sexual assault as he heads toward election fight with Trump|work=[[CNBC]]|date=April 14, 2020 | access-date=April 15, 2020|first=Dan|last=Mangan}}</ref>\n\nOn April 12, 2020, ''The New York Times'' released an analysis of their investigative reporting in which they interviewed Reade, several of her friends, lawyers, nearly two dozen people who worked with Biden in the early 1990s, and the seven women who accused Biden of kissing, hugging, or touching them in ways that had made them feel uncomfortable. No other allegations about sexual assault surfaced in the course of this reporting, nor did any former Biden staff members corroborate any details of Reade's allegation, although several of the seven women stated that they believed Reade but had no new knowledge of the incident.<ref name=\"nyt\" /> Two friends of Reade confirmed to ''The New York Times'' that she had told them of the alleged assault (one in 1993 shortly after the alleged assault took place, the other in 2008). Reade's brother has also publicly stated that she had told him about it,<ref name=\"nyt\" /> initially saying that Reade told him that Biden had touched her neck and shoulders, but several days later he told ''The Washington Post'' that he also remembered that she had said that Biden had reached \"under her clothes.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ruth|first1=Marcus|title=Assessing Tara Reade's allegations|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2020/04/15/seriousness-flaws-tara-reades-allegations/|website=The Washington Post |access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n''The New York Times'' reporters additionally interviewed the chief and deputy-chief of Biden's Senate staff during 1992 and 1993 as well as its long-term executive assistant. They expressed their doubts as to the veracity of Reade's account, arguing that that they would have recalled Reade's complaints about Biden's conduct had she made them while also asserting that the behavior alleged would be out of character for him. Melissa Lefko, then a staff assistant for Biden, told the reporters that she had never experienced harassment and Biden's office was a \"very supportive environment for women.\" \"When you work on the Hill, everyone knows who the good guys are and who the bad guys are, and Biden was a good guy,\" Lefko stated as well.<ref name=\"nyt\" />\n\n== Media coverage ==\nThe allegations, and the delayed response by major media publications, stirred mixed sentiments on both the left and right of the American political spectrum.<ref name=Walsh-200415>{{cite news|url=https://www.thenation.com/article/politics/tara-reade-joe-biden-democrats/|title=The Troublesome Tara Reade Story|work=[[The Nation]]|date=April 15, 2020 | access-date=April 16, 2020|first=Joan|last=Walsh}}</ref> On March 28, 2020, ''The Guardian'' columnist Arwa Mahdawi wrote about how right-wing media outlets embraced the controversy, remarking that \"It is hugely frustrating to see conservatives, who couldn't give a damn about the multiple sexual assault allegations against Donald Trump, weaponize the accusations against Biden.\" She added that she found it \"also frustrating to see so many liberals turning a blind eye\" to a serious allegation.<ref name=\"TheWeek-200416\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theweek.co.uk/106651/joe-biden-the-sexual-assault-claim-dividing-democrats|title=Joe Biden: the sexual assault claim dividing Democrats|date=April 16, 2020|work=[[The Week]]|access-date=April 16, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Mahdawi-200328>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/28/joe-biden-sexual-assault-allegations-why-has-media-ignored-claims|title=Why has the media ignored sexual assault and misbehaviour allegations against Biden?|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=March 28, 2020 | access-date=April 16, 2020|first=Arwa|last=Mahdawi}}</ref>\n\n''The New York Times'' was criticized by other media outlets for its delayed coverage of the allegation, and how it differed from reporting on other allegations in the past.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nationalreview.com/corner/dean-baquet-makes-no-sense/|title=Dean Baquet Makes No Sense|last=Hirschauer|first=John|date=April 15, 2020|website=National Review|url-status=live|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jacobinmag.com/2020/04/joe-biden-tara-reade-sexual-assault-allegation-media|title=The Media Had a Formula for Reporting Sexual Misconduct. Then Joe Biden Was Accused.|last=Marcetic|first=Branko|date=April 14, 2020|website=Jacobin Magazine|url-status=live|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2020/04/media-floodgates-open-joe-biden-tara-reade-allegation|title=The Media Floodgates Finally Open on Biden Sexual Assault Allegation|last=Ecarma|first=Caleb|date=April 14, 2020|website=Vanity Fair|url-status=live|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2020/04/joe-biden-harassment-nytimes.html|title=Joe Biden Sails Under the New York Times' Bar for Sexual Abuse|last=Cauterucci|first=Christina|date=April 13, 2020|website=Slate|url-status=live|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>  Its executive editor, [[Dean Baquet]], published  an [[op-ed]] on April 13, 2020 responding to various criticisms including that his newspaper was slow to publish coverage of the news story.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nationalreview.com/2020/04/the-new-york-times-denies-tara-reade-the-christine-blasey-ford-treatment/|title=The New York Times Denies Tara Reade the Christine Blasey Ford Treatment|date=April 14, 2020|website=National Review|language=en-US|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2020/04/joe-biden-harassment-nytimes.html|title=Joe Biden Sails Under the New York Times' Bar for Sexual Abuse|last=Cauterucci|first=Christina|date=April 13, 2020|website=Slate Magazine|language=en|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2020/04/media-floodgates-open-joe-biden-tara-reade-allegation|title=The Media Floodgates Finally Open on Biden Sexual Assault Allegation|last=Ecarma|first=Caleb|website=Vanity Fair|language=en|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|last=Smith|first=Ben|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/13/business/media/joe-biden-tara-reade-new-york-times.html|title=The Times Took 19 Days to Report an Accusation Against Biden. Here's Why.|date=April 13, 2020|work=The New York Times|access-date=April 15, 2020|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> In an interview with the newspaper's media columnist [[Ben Smith (journalist)|Ben Smith]], Baquet responded to a controversy about a line in the news story that was removed after the piece's initial publication. The sentence previously read: \"The Times found no pattern of sexual misconduct by Mr. Biden, beyond the hugs, kisses and touching that women previously said made them uncomfortable.\" Baquet explained that it had been included originally in order not to falsely imply that other individuals had made allegations of as invasive in nature as Reade's but thereafter removed because of \"awkward phrasing issue that could be read different ways.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/media/492680-ny-times-faces-blowback-for-removal-of-controversial-passage-on-biden-sexual|title=NY Times faces blowback for removal of controversial passage on Biden sexual assault allegation|last=Swanson|first=Ian|date=April 14, 2020|website=The Hill|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref> Baquet stated that the edit was made after [[Joe Biden 2020 presidential campaign|the Biden campaign]] had objected to it because \"[it] made it look like there were other instances in which he had been accused of sexual misconduct.\".<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Reactions ==\nOn April 14, 2020, in an online conversation with [[The Wing (workspace)|The Wing]], [[United States House of Representatives|U.S. Representative]] [[Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez]] said that it was legitimate to discuss Reade's allegation against Biden.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/alexandria-ocasio-cortez-joe-biden-its-legitimate-to-talk-about-allegations/|title=Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez: \"It's legitimate to talk about\" allegations against Joe Biden|website=www.cbsnews.com|language=en-US|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/alexandria-ocasio-cortez-sexual-assault-allegation-joe-biden-news-a9466051.html|title=AOC says it's 'legitimate to talk about' sexual assault allegation against Joe Biden|date=April 15, 2020|website=The Independent|language=en|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== External link ==\n*{{Cite web|first=Katie|last=Halper|authorlink=|title=Biden accuser: \"I wanted to be a senator; I didn't want to sleep with one\" (audio)|website=Katie Halper podcast|date=March 30, 2020|url=https://soundcloud.com/katie-halper/tara-to-post|access-date=}}\n{{Joe Biden}}\n\n[[Category:2020 controversies]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in the United States]]\n[[Category:Sexual assaults in the United States]]\n[[Category:Media-related controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:Joe Biden 2020 presidential campaign|Assault allegation]]\n", "text_old": "<noinclude>{{User:RMCD bot/subject notice|1=?|2=Talk:Joe Biden sexual assault allegation#Requested move 14 April 2020 }}\n</noinclude><!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Joe Biden assault allegation|timestamp=20200412194501|year=2020|month=April|day=12|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Joe Biden assault allegation|date=12 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Redirect|Tara Reade|the actress|Tara Reid}}\n{{Use American English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\nIn March 2020, Alexandra Tara Reade alleged that [[Joe Biden]] had sexually assaulted her when she was a senate aide in 1993.<ref name=InterceptTimesup>{{cite news|url=https://theintercept.com/2020/03/24/joe-biden-metoo-times-up/|first=Ryan|last=Grim|title=Time's Up Said It Could Not Fund a #MeToo Allegation Against Joe Biden, Citing Its Nonprofit Status and His Presidential Run|website=[[The Intercept]]|date=March 24, 2020 |access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref><ref name=vox>{{cite news|url=https://www.vox.com/2020/3/27/21195935/joe-biden-sexual-assault-allegation|last=North|first=Anna|title=A sexual assault allegation against Joe Biden has ignited a firestorm of controversy|website=[[Vox (website)|Vox]]|date=March 27, 2020 |access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://thehill.com/hilltv/rising/489719-tara-reade-discusses-biden-allegation-with-hilltvs-rising|title=Tara Reade discusses Biden allegation with Hill.TV's 'Rising'|newspaper=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]]|date=March 26, 2020 |access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/rose-mcgowan-alyssa-milano-joe-biden-alexandra-tara-reade-kavanaugh-a9454256.html|last=White|first=Adam|title=Rose McGowan calls Charmed co-star Alyssa Milano 'a fraud' for endorsing Joe Biden|newspaper=[[The Independent]]|date=April 8, 2020 <!-- From the timestamp in the HTML source --> |access-date=April 9, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Halper|first=Katie|url=https://www.currentaffairs.org/2020/03/tara-reade-tells-her-story|title=Tara Reade Tells Her Story|date=March 31, 2020|magazine=[[Current Affairs (magazine)|Current Affairs]]|access-date=April 9, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> A Biden spokesperson said the allegation was false.<ref name=nyt>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/12/us/politics/joe-biden-tara-reade-sexual-assault-complaint.html|last=Lerer|first=Lisa|last2=Ember|first2=Sydney|title=Examining Tara Reade's Sexual Assault Allegation Against Joe Biden|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=April 12, 2020 |access-date=April 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\n[[File:SenareaidIDTaraReade.webp|thumb|U.S. Senate Identification Badge photo of Reade she provided to the ''[[New York Times]]'']]\nAlexandra Tara Reade is resident of California, having been born there circa 1964.<ref name=\"WE200415\">{{cite web|last1=Larsen|first1=Emily|title=Everything we know about the Biden sexual assault allegation|url=https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/news/everything-we-know-about-the-biden-sexual-assault-allegation|publisher=Washington Examiner |access-date=April 16, 2020|date=April 15, 2020}}</ref>  She was an actress and a model in her early life.<ref name=\"WE200415\" />  When she was 29, she was a staff assistant in the office of then Senator Joe Biden from December 1992 to August 1993.<ref name=\"WE200415\" />\n\nAccording to the ''Washington Examiner,'' after working in Washington, she left and became a mother, but changed her name multiple times after leaving an abusive marriage.<ref name=\"WE200415\" />  She earned a law degree from [[Seattle University School of Law]], but has not practiced law.<ref name=\"WE200415\" />  She has worked as a [[victims rights]] advocate and with families who have special needs children.<ref name=\"WE200415\" />  She has also testified as an expert witness in court.<ref name=\"WE200415\" />\n\n== Allegations ==\nDuring an interview with a reporter in April 2019, Reade alleged that Biden touched her inappropriately and sexual harassed her while she worked in his U.S. Senate office.  Reade made the allegation after watching an episode of the ''[[The View (talk show)|The View]]'' on April 1, 2019 in which Nevada politician [[Lucy Flores]] had alleged that Biden sniffed her hair and kissed the back of her head shortly before a political rally in 2014.<ref name=InterceptTimesup /><ref name=InterceptTimesup /><ref>{{Cite news|first=Alan|last=Riquelmy|authorlink=|title=Nevada County woman says Joe Biden inappropriately touched her while working in his U.S. Senate office|newspaper=[[The Union (newspaper)|The Union]]|date=April 3, 2019|url=https://www.theunion.com/news/nevada-county-woman-says-joe-biden-inappropriately-touched-her-while-working-in-his-u-s-senate-office/ |access-date=April 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\nDuring an interview with Katie Halper which was released as a podcast on March 25, 2020, Reade alleged that Biden had pushed her against a wall and penetrated her with his finger in a [[Capitol Hill]] office building in 1993.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.salon.com/2020/03/31/a-woman-accuses-joe-biden-of-sexual-assault-and-all-hell-breaks-loose-online-heres-what-we-know/|title=A woman accuses Joe Biden of sexual assault, and all hell breaks loose online. Here's what we know|last=Marcotte|first=Amanda|date=March 31, 2020|website=Salon|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref>  On April 9, 2020, she filed a police report with the Washington, D.C. police alleging she was sexually assaulted between March 1 and May 31, 1993.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Vitali|first1=Ali|last2=Memoli|first2=Mike|title=Woman broadens claims against Biden to include sexual assault|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/woman-broadens-claims-against-biden-include-sexual-assault-n1182296 |access-date=April 16, 2020|work=NBC News|date=April 12, 2020}}</ref> Reade stated that the report was about Biden. She acknowledged that the statute of limitations has lapsed, and that she filed the report \"for safety reasons only\".<ref name=vox /><ref name=\"nyt\" /><ref name=Mangan-200414>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/04/14/joe-biden-accused-of-sex-assault-amid-challenge-to-donald-trump.html|title=Joe Biden is accused of sexual assault as he heads toward election fight with Trump|work=[[CNBC]]|date=April 14, 2020 | access-date=April 15, 2020|first=Dan|last=Mangan}}</ref>\n\nOn April 12, 2020, ''The New York Times'' released an analysis of their investigative reporting in which they interviewed Reade, several of her friends, lawyers, nearly two dozen people who worked with Biden in the early 1990s, and the seven women who accused Biden of kissing, hugging, or touching them in ways that had made them feel uncomfortable. No other allegations about sexual assault surfaced in the course of this reporting, nor did any former Biden staff members corroborate any details of Reade's allegation, although several of the seven women stated that they believed Reade but had no new knowledge of the incident.<ref name=\"nyt\" /> Two friends of Reade confirmed to ''The New York Times'' that she had told them of the alleged assault (one in 1993 shortly after the alleged assault took place, the other in 2008). Reade's brother has also publicly stated that she had told him about it,<ref name=\"nyt\" /> initially saying that Reade told him that Biden had touched her neck and shoulders, but several days later he told ''The Washington Post'' that he also remembered that she had said that Biden had reached \"under her clothes.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ruth|first1=Marcus|title=Assessing Tara Reade's allegations|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2020/04/15/seriousness-flaws-tara-reades-allegations/|website=The Washington Post |access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n''The New York Times'' reporters additionally interviewed the chief and deputy-chief of Biden's Senate staff during 1992 and 1993 as well as its long-term executive assistant. They expressed their doubts as to the veracity of Reade's account, arguing that that they would have recalled Reade's complaints about Biden's conduct had she made them while also asserting that the behavior alleged would be out of character for him. Melissa Lefko, then a staff assistant for Biden, told the reporters that she had never experienced harassment and Biden's office was a \"very supportive environment for women.\" \"When you work on the Hill, everyone knows who the good guys are and who the bad guys are, and Biden was a good guy,\" Lefko stated as well.<ref name=\"nyt\" />\n\n== Media coverage ==\nThe allegations, and the delayed response by major media publications, stirred mixed sentiments on both the left and right of the American political spectrum.<ref name=Walsh-200415>{{cite news|url=https://www.thenation.com/article/politics/tara-reade-joe-biden-democrats/|title=The Troublesome Tara Reade Story|work=[[The Nation]]|date=April 15, 2020 | access-date=April 16, 2020|first=Joan|last=Walsh}}</ref> On March 28, 2020, ''The Guardian'' columnist Arwa Mahdawi wrote about how right-wing media outlets embraced the controversy, remarking that \"It is hugely frustrating to see conservatives, who couldn't give a damn about the multiple sexual assault allegations against Donald Trump, weaponize the accusations against Biden.\" She added that she found it \"also frustrating to see so many liberals turning a blind eye\" to a serious allegation.<ref name=\"TheWeek-200416\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theweek.co.uk/106651/joe-biden-the-sexual-assault-claim-dividing-democrats|title=Joe Biden: the sexual assault claim dividing Democrats|date=April 16, 2020|work=[[The Week]]|access-date=April 16, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Mahdawi-200328>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/28/joe-biden-sexual-assault-allegations-why-has-media-ignored-claims|title=Why has the media ignored sexual assault and misbehaviour allegations against Biden?|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=March 28, 2020 | access-date=April 16, 2020|first=Arwa|last=Mahdawi}}</ref>\n\n''The New York Times'' was criticized by other media outlets for its delayed coverage of the allegation, and how it differed from reporting on other allegations in the past.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nationalreview.com/corner/dean-baquet-makes-no-sense/|title=Dean Baquet Makes No Sense|last=Hirschauer|first=John|date=April 15, 2020|website=National Review|url-status=live|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jacobinmag.com/2020/04/joe-biden-tara-reade-sexual-assault-allegation-media|title=The Media Had a Formula for Reporting Sexual Misconduct. Then Joe Biden Was Accused.|last=Marcetic|first=Branko|date=April 14, 2020|website=Jacobin Magazine|url-status=live|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2020/04/media-floodgates-open-joe-biden-tara-reade-allegation|title=The Media Floodgates Finally Open on Biden Sexual Assault Allegation|last=Ecarma|first=Caleb|date=April 14, 2020|website=Vanity Fair|url-status=live|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2020/04/joe-biden-harassment-nytimes.html|title=Joe Biden Sails Under the New York Times' Bar for Sexual Abuse|last=Cauterucci|first=Christina|date=April 13, 2020|website=Slate|url-status=live|access-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>  Its executive editor, [[Dean Baquet]], published  an [[op-ed]] on April 13, 2020 responding to various criticisms including that his newspaper was slow to publish coverage of the news story.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nationalreview.com/2020/04/the-new-york-times-denies-tara-reade-the-christine-blasey-ford-treatment/|title=The New York Times Denies Tara Reade the Christine Blasey Ford Treatment|date=April 14, 2020|website=National Review|language=en-US|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2020/04/joe-biden-harassment-nytimes.html|title=Joe Biden Sails Under the New York Times' Bar for Sexual Abuse|last=Cauterucci|first=Christina|date=April 13, 2020|website=Slate Magazine|language=en|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2020/04/media-floodgates-open-joe-biden-tara-reade-allegation|title=The Media Floodgates Finally Open on Biden Sexual Assault Allegation|last=Ecarma|first=Caleb|website=Vanity Fair|language=en|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|last=Smith|first=Ben|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/13/business/media/joe-biden-tara-reade-new-york-times.html|title=The Times Took 19 Days to Report an Accusation Against Biden. Here's Why.|date=April 13, 2020|work=The New York Times|access-date=April 15, 2020|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> In an interview with the newspaper's media columnist [[Ben Smith (journalist)|Ben Smith]], Baquet responded to a controversy about a line in the news story that was removed after the piece's initial publication. The sentence previously read: \"The Times found no pattern of sexual misconduct by Mr. Biden, beyond the hugs, kisses and touching that women previously said made them uncomfortable.\" Baquet explained that it had been included originally in order not to falsely imply that other individuals had made allegations of as invasive in nature as Reade's but thereafter removed because of \"awkward phrasing issue that could be read different ways.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/media/492680-ny-times-faces-blowback-for-removal-of-controversial-passage-on-biden-sexual|title=NY Times faces blowback for removal of controversial passage on Biden sexual assault allegation|last=Swanson|first=Ian|date=April 14, 2020|website=The Hill|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref> Baquet stated that the edit was made after [[Joe Biden 2020 presidential campaign|the Biden campaign]] had objected to it because \"[it] made it look like there were other instances in which he had been accused of sexual misconduct.\".<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Reactions ==\nOn April 14, 2020, in an online conversation with [[The Wing (workspace)|The Wing]], [[United States House of Representatives|U.S. Representative]] [[Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez]] said that it was legitimate to discuss Reade's allegation against Biden.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/alexandria-ocasio-cortez-joe-biden-its-legitimate-to-talk-about-allegations/|title=Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez: \"It's legitimate to talk about\" allegations against Joe Biden|website=www.cbsnews.com|language=en-US|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/alexandria-ocasio-cortez-sexual-assault-allegation-joe-biden-news-a9466051.html|title=AOC says it's 'legitimate to talk about' sexual assault allegation against Joe Biden|date=April 15, 2020|website=The Independent|language=en|access-date=April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{Cite web|first=Katie|last=Halper|authorlink=|title=Biden accuser: \"I wanted to be a senator; I didn't want to sleep with one\" (audio)|website=Katie Halper podcast|date=March 30, 2020|url=https://soundcloud.com/katie-halper/tara-to-post  |access-date=}}\n{{Joe Biden}}\n\n[[Category:2020 controversies]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in the United States]]\n[[Category:Sexual assaults in the United States]]\n[[Category:Media-related controversies in the United States]]\n[[Category:Joe Biden 2020 presidential campaign|Assault allegation]]\n", "name_user": "CoffeeWithMarkets", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joe_Biden_sexual_assault_allegation"}
{"title_page": "Qontis", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=October 2019}}\n\n{{short description|Online personal finance platform based in Switzerland}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name             = Qontis\n| logo             = \n| logo_caption     = \n| image            = \n| image_caption    = \n| trading_name     = <!-- d/b/a/, doing business as - if different from legal name above -->\n| native_name      = <!-- Company's name in home country language -->\n| native_name_lang = <!-- Use ISO 639-2 code, e.g. \"fr\" for French. If there is more than one native name, in different languages, enter those names using {{tl|lang}}, instead. -->\n| romanized        = \n| former type      = \n| type             = \n| traded_as        = \n| industry         = [[Personal finance|Personal Finance Management]]\n| genre            = <!-- Only used with media and publishing companies -->\n| fate             = \n| predecessor      = \n| successor        = \n| foundation       = 2013\n| founder          = ''[[Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung]]'', Crealogix\n| defunct          = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| location_city    = \n| location_country = [[Switzerland]]\n| locations        = <!-- Number of locations, stores, offices, etc. -->\n| area_served      = \n| key_people       = {{Plainlist |\n*Christian Bieri (CEO) \n*Nils Reimelt (CMO) \n*Walter Meister (Board of Directors)\n}}\n| products         = Personal finance management solutions, online financial content\n| production       = \n| services         = \n| revenue          = \n| operating_income = \n| net_income       = \n| aum              = <!-- Only used with financial services companies -->\n| assets           = \n| equity           = \n| owner            = \n| num_employees    = \n| parent           = \n| divisions        = \n| subsid           = \n| homepage         = {{URL|qontis.ch}}\n| footnotes        = \n| intl             = \n| bodystyle        = \n}}\n'''Qontis''' is a [[Switzerland]] based online [[Personal finance|personal finance management (PFM)]] [[Computing platform|platform]]. The service is part of a commercial enterprise between the ''[[Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung]]'' media property and e-banking solutions provider Crealogix. The platform provides users with the ability to document and organize data from all instances of private income and expenditures.<ref name=nzz13>{{Citation | url = http://www.nzz.ch/meinung/in-eigener-sache/nzz-gruendet-plattform-fuer-private-finanzverwaltung-1.18130158| title = NZZ based platform for private financial management| publisher = [[Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung]]| date = August 9, 2013| accessdate = January 17, 2014}}</ref> Qontis' [[CEO (chief executive officer)]] is Christian Bieri, who formerly served as the Austrian Country Manager and CEE for the Vienna branch of [[Avaloq]] Evolution AG. The company's [[Chief marketing officer|CMO (chief marketing officer)]] is Nils Reimelt, the former digital director at [[Ringier#Ringier Axel Springer Media AG|Ringier Axel Springer Media AG]].<ref name=fin13>{{Citation | url =http://www.finews.ch/news/12806-qontis-personal-finance-plattform-schweiz | title =New personal finance platform in Switzerland | publisher = Finnews.ch| date = August 9, 2013 | accessdate = January 17, 2014}}</ref><ref name=zurichoberlander13>{{Citation | url = http://www.zol.ch/bezirk-hinwil/bubikon/NZZ-und-Crealogix-arbeiten-zusammen/story/30225812| title = NZZ and Crealogix work together| publisher = [[Z\u00fcrcher Oberl\u00e4nder]]| date = August 9, 2013| accessdate = January 17, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Citation |url=http://www.knip.ch/news/detail/finanz-megatrend-interview-qontis |title= Zum Launch des PFM von Qontis - Fragen an CMO Nils Reimelt |publisher=Knip |date = 13 March 2014 | author = Christina Kehl | accessdate=13 March 2014}}</ref> In March 2014, Qontis developed a personal Finance Manager, which should be able to access the data of almost all Swiss (\"[[multibanking]]\").<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.netzwoche.ch/news/2014-03-14/qontis-lanciert-multibanking-personal-finance-manager|title=Qontis lanciert Multibanking Personal Finance Manager|website=www.netzwoche.ch|language=de|access-date=2018-06-07}}</ref>\n\n==Features==\nIn addition to providing an overview of personal finance details, some of the features that Qontis offers include budgeting tools that can analyze a user's transaction history, cost optimization suggestions, and [[capital accumulation]] support.<ref name=nzz13 />\n<ref name=cash13>{{Citation | url = http://www.cash.ch/news/alle/nzz_und_crealogix_lancieren_personal_finance_plattform_qontis-3111505-448| title = NZZ and Crealogix launch personal finance platform Qontis| publisher = Cash.ch| date = August 9, 2013| accessdate = January 17, 2014}}</ref>\n<ref name=ictjournal13>{{Citation | url = http://www.ictjournal.ch/News/2013/08/09/NZZ-et-Crealogix-creent-une-co-entreprise-de-finances-personnelles.aspx| title = NZZ Crealogix and create a joint venture Personal Finance| publisher = ICT Journal| date = | accessdate = January 17, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Online magazine===\nQontis also publishes an online magazine with editorial contributions that are relevant to the financial areas of planning, saving, and spending.<ref name=Computerworld13>{{Citation | url = http://www.computerworld.ch/news/it-branche/artikel/crealogix-und-nzz-planen-finanzportal-63974/| title =Crealogix and NZZ plan Financial Portal | publisher = Computerworld.ch| date = August 9, 2013| accessdate = January 17, 2014}}</ref> The content is intended to assist users in improving their daily spending habits.<ref name=moneycab13>{{Citation | url =http://www.moneycab.com/mcc/2013/08/09/nzz-und-crealogix-lancieren-bankenuebergreifende-personal-finance-plattform/ | title = NZZ und Crealogix lancieren banken\u00fcbergreifende Personal Finance Plattform| publisher = Moneycab| date = August 9, 2013| accessdate = January 17, 2014}}</ref> Qontis released the first issue of its magazine in the summer of 2013, approximately three months before the platform itself was available.<ref name=moneycab13 />\n\n==Partnerships==\nThe venture between the NZZ and Crealogix has led to partnerships with companies such as Comparis, Moneypark, and MyDepotCheck.<ref name=ictjournal13 /><ref name=Computerworld13 /><ref name=inside-it.ch>{{Citation | url =http://www.inside-it.ch/articles/33381 | title = Personal Finance: NZZ and Crealogix build new platform| publisher = inside-it| date = August 9, 2013| accessdate = January 17, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160226083937/http://www.qontis.com/ Qontis.com]\n\n[[Category:Personal finance]]\n[[Category:Financial technology companies]]\n[[Category:Swiss companies established in 2013]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=October 2019}}\n\n{{short description|Online personal finance platform based in Switzerland}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name             = Qontis\n| logo             = \n| logo_caption     = \n| image            = \n| image_caption    = \n| trading_name     = <!-- d/b/a/, doing business as - if different from legal name above -->\n| native_name      = <!-- Company's name in home country language -->\n| native_name_lang = <!-- Use ISO 639-2 code, e.g. \"fr\" for French. If there is more than one native name, in different languages, enter those names using {{tl|lang}}, instead. -->\n| romanized        = \n| former type      = \n| type             = \n| traded_as        = \n| industry         = [[Personal finance|Personal Finance Management]]\n| genre            = <!-- Only used with media and publishing companies -->\n| fate             = \n| predecessor      = \n| successor        = \n| foundation       = 2013\n| founder          = ''[[Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung]]'', Crealogix\n| defunct          = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| location_city    = \n| location_country = [[Switzerland]]\n| locations        = <!-- Number of locations, stores, offices, etc. -->\n| area_served      = \n| key_people       = {{Plainlist |\n*Christian Bieri (CEO) \n*Nils Reimelt (CMO) \n*Walter Meister (Board of Directors)\n}}\n| products         = Personal finance management solutions, online financial content\n| production       = \n| services         = \n| revenue          = \n| operating_income = \n| net_income       = \n| aum              = <!-- Only used with financial services companies -->\n| assets           = \n| equity           = \n| owner            = \n| num_employees    = \n| parent           = \n| divisions        = \n| subsid           = \n| homepage         = {{URL|qontis.ch}}\n| footnotes        = \n| intl             = \n| bodystyle        = \n}}\n'''Qontis''' is a [[Switzerland]] based online [[Personal finance|personal finance management (PFM)]] [[Computing platform|platform]]. The service is part of a commercial enterprise between the ''[[Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung]]'' media property and e-banking solutions provider Crealogix. The platform provides users with the ability to document and organize data from all instances of private income and expenditures.<ref name=nzz13>{{Citation | url = http://www.nzz.ch/meinung/in-eigener-sache/nzz-gruendet-plattform-fuer-private-finanzverwaltung-1.18130158| title = NZZ based platform for private financial management| publisher = [[Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung]]| date = August 9, 2013| accessdate = January 17, 2014}}</ref> Qontis' [[CEO (chief executive officer)]] is Christian Bieri, who formerly served as the Austrian Country Manager and CEE for the Vienna branch of [[Avaloq]] Evolution AG. The company's [[Chief marketing officer|CMO (chief marketing officer)]] is Nils Reimelt, the former digital director at [[Ringier#Ringier Axel Springer Media AG|Ringier Axel Springer Media AG]].<ref name=fin13>{{Citation | url =http://www.finews.ch/news/12806-qontis-personal-finance-plattform-schweiz | title =New personal finance platform in Switzerland | publisher = Finnews.ch| date = August 9, 2013 | accessdate = January 17, 2014}}</ref><ref name=zurichoberlander13>{{Citation | url = http://www.zol.ch/bezirk-hinwil/bubikon/NZZ-und-Crealogix-arbeiten-zusammen/story/30225812| title = NZZ and Crealogix work together| publisher = [[Z\u00fcrcher Oberl\u00e4nder]]| date = August 9, 2013| accessdate = January 17, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Citation |url=http://www.knip.ch/news/detail/finanz-megatrend-interview-qontis |title= Zum Launch des PFM von Qontis - Fragen an CMO Nils Reimelt |publisher=Knip |date = 13 March 2014 | author = Christina Kehl | accessdate=13 March 2014}}</ref> In March 2014, Qontis developed a personal Finance Manager, which should be able to access the data of almost all Swiss.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.netzwoche.ch/news/2014-03-14/qontis-lanciert-multibanking-personal-finance-manager|title=Qontis lanciert Multibanking Personal Finance Manager|website=www.netzwoche.ch|language=de|access-date=2018-06-07}}</ref>\n\n==Features==\nIn addition to providing an overview of personal finance details, some of the features that Qontis offers include budgeting tools that can analyze a user's transaction history, cost optimization suggestions, and [[capital accumulation]] support.<ref name=nzz13 />\n<ref name=cash13>{{Citation | url = http://www.cash.ch/news/alle/nzz_und_crealogix_lancieren_personal_finance_plattform_qontis-3111505-448| title = NZZ and Crealogix launch personal finance platform Qontis| publisher = Cash.ch| date = August 9, 2013| accessdate = January 17, 2014}}</ref>\n<ref name=ictjournal13>{{Citation | url = http://www.ictjournal.ch/News/2013/08/09/NZZ-et-Crealogix-creent-une-co-entreprise-de-finances-personnelles.aspx| title = NZZ Crealogix and create a joint venture Personal Finance| publisher = ICT Journal| date = | accessdate = January 17, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Online magazine===\nQontis also publishes an online magazine with editorial contributions that are relevant to the financial areas of planning, saving, and spending.<ref name=Computerworld13>{{Citation | url = http://www.computerworld.ch/news/it-branche/artikel/crealogix-und-nzz-planen-finanzportal-63974/| title =Crealogix and NZZ plan Financial Portal | publisher = Computerworld.ch| date = August 9, 2013| accessdate = January 17, 2014}}</ref> The content is intended to assist users in improving their daily spending habits.<ref name=moneycab13>{{Citation | url =http://www.moneycab.com/mcc/2013/08/09/nzz-und-crealogix-lancieren-bankenuebergreifende-personal-finance-plattform/ | title = NZZ und Crealogix lancieren banken\u00fcbergreifende Personal Finance Plattform| publisher = Moneycab| date = August 9, 2013| accessdate = January 17, 2014}}</ref> Qontis released the first issue of its magazine in the summer of 2013, approximately three months before the platform itself was available.<ref name=moneycab13 />\n\n==Partnerships==\nThe venture between the NZZ and Crealogix has led to partnerships with companies such as Comparis, Moneypark, and MyDepotCheck.<ref name=ictjournal13 /><ref name=Computerworld13 /><ref name=inside-it.ch>{{Citation | url =http://www.inside-it.ch/articles/33381 | title = Personal Finance: NZZ and Crealogix build new platform| publisher = inside-it| date = August 9, 2013| accessdate = January 17, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160226083937/http://www.qontis.com/ Qontis.com]\n\n[[Category:Personal finance]]\n[[Category:Financial technology companies]]\n[[Category:Swiss companies established in 2013]]\n", "name_user": "Kku", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:l", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qontis"}
{"title_page": "Sri Lanka", "text_new": "{{redirect|Ceylon}}\n{{pp|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Island country in South Asia}}\n{{coord|7|N|81|E|region:LK_type:country_source:dewiki|display=title}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox country\n| conventional_long_name = {{lang|en|Democratic Socialist Republic of {{nowrap|Sri Lanka}}}}\n| common_name = Sri Lanka\n| native_name = {{ubl|{{native name|si|\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3 \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0da2\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dcf\u0da2\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0da2\u0db1\u0dbb\u0da2\u0dba|italics=off}}\n            |''Sr\u012b Lank\u0101 praj\u0101t\u0101ntrika sam\u0101jav\u0101d\u012b janarajaya''\n            |{{native name|ta|\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0ba9\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0baf\u0b95 \u0b9a\u0bcb\u0b9a\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0b95\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bc1|italics=off}}\n            |''Ila\u1e45kai ca\u1e49an\u0101yaka c\u014dcalicak ku\u1e6diyaracu''\n }}\n| image_flag = Flag of Sri Lanka.svg\n| image_coat = Emblem of Sri Lanka.svg\n| symbol_width = 50px\n| symbol_type = Emblem\n| national_motto = \n| national_anthem = \"[[Sri Lanka Matha]]\"<br />({{Lang-en|\"Mother Sri Lanka\"}})<br />[[File:Sri Lankan national anthem, performed by the United States Navy Band.oga|center]]\n| image_map = Sri Lanka (orthographic projection).svg\n| image_map2 = Sri Lanka - Location Map (2011) - LKA - UNOCHA.svg\n| capital = [[Sri Jayawardenepura Kotte]]\n| coordinates = {{Coord|6|56|N|79|52|E|type:city}}\n| largest_city = [[Colombo]]\n| official_languages = [[Sinhala language|Sinhala]]<br/>[[Tamil language|Tamil]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.languagesdept.gov.lk/web/|title=Department of Official Languages|publisher=}}</ref>\n| languages_sub = yes\n| languages2_type = Recognised languages\n| languages2 = [[Sri Lankan English|English]]\n| ethnic